This paper is primarily focused on analyzing the performance of convolutional neural networks (convnets) in object detection tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the design choices involved in convnet architecture, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of image renderings for data augmentation, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
